,000) of annual Gaming Revenue, 5.5% of annual Gaming Revenue in excess of Twelve Million Dollars ($12,000,000) but less than or equal to Fifteen Million Dollars ($15,000,000), and 4.5% of annual Gaming Revenue in excess of Fifteen Million Dollars ($15,000,000). In all cases, the Percentage Rent shall be reduced by the rent paid by California Prospectors, L.L.C. under and pursuant to the California Lottery Station Lease. Last Chance shall pay Minimum Annual Rent in twelve (12) equal monthly installments (except as provided above) during each year of the Lease Term, on the first day of each calendar month following the Closing."}],"coordinates":[],"confidence":{"state":"pre-added","who":["user:terezalat"],"prob":1},"fields":{},"normalizations":{}},{"classId":"e_18","part":"s1p88","offsets":[{"start":0,"text":"3.2"}],"coordinates":[],"confidence":{"state":"pre-added","who":["user:terezalat"],"prob":1},"fields":{},"normalizations":{}},{"classId":"e_17","part":"s1p88","offsets":[{"start":4,"text":"Percentage Rent."}],"coordinates":[],"confidence":{"state":"pre-added","who":["user:terezalat"],"prob":1},"fields":{},"normalizations":{}},{"classId":"e_9","part":"s1p89","offsets":[{"start":16,"text":"Percentage Rent shall be payable monthly, in arrears, commencing with the calendar month following the month in which Gaming Revenue first exceeds the Minimum Annual Rent for such fiscal year, PROVIDED, HOWEVER, that there shall be no payment or accrual of Percentage Rent until Landlord shall have satisfied the gaming licensing requirements of Section 3.2(C) and any and all requirements of Chapter 463 of the Nevada Revised Statutes and the Regulations of the Nevada Gaming Commission, the State Gaming Control Board and Washoe County, Nevada."}],"coordinates":[],"confidence":{"state":"pre-added","who":["user:terezalat"],"prob":1},"fields":{},"normalizations":{}},{"classId":"e_18","part":"s1p96","offsets":[{"start":0,"text":"3.3"}],"coordinates":[],"confidence":{"state":"pre-added"